title: Lowest Primary School Repetition Rate
description: In 2018, Uzbekistan had one of the lowest primary school repetition rates in the world, with only 0.00125% of total enrollment repeating a grade.

title: High Educational Attainment in Lower Secondary
description: As of 2022, 100% of the male population aged 25 and older in Uzbekistan had completed at least lower secondary education, one of the highest rates globally.

title: High Gender Equality Rating
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan achieved a CPIA gender equality rating of 4.5, indicating a strong commitment to gender equality.

title: High Revenue Mobilization Efficiency
description: Uzbekistan scored 4.5 in the CPIA efficiency of revenue mobilization rating in 2023, reflecting effective revenue collection practices.

title: High Customs and Import Duties
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan collected 11,126,911,928,350 LCU in customs and other import duties, one of the highest figures globally.

title: High Compensation of Employees
description: The compensation of employees in Uzbekistan reached 60,189,419,334,713.6 LCU in 2023, indicating significant government expenditure in this area.

title: High Other Expenses
description: In 2023, Uzbekistan's other expenses amounted to 61,285,584,505,848.5 LCU, reflecting substantial spending in various sectors.

title: High Net Borrowing
description: Uzbekistan's net borrowing was -51,491,089,426,083.6 LCU in 2023, indicating a significant budget deficit.
